achieves this objective.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-71379","V-57119"],"ccis":["CCI-001879"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"00d70204-ed95-4f8e-9016-13e0ab1b5b18","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-207460","group_tree":[{"id":"V-207460","title":"SRG-OS-000352","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-207460","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM must provide a report generation capability that supports after-the-fact investigations of security incidents.","rule_id_src":"SV-207460r958774_rule","rule_id":"SV-207460r958774","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000352-VMM-001300","rule_title":"The VMM must provide a report generation capability that supports after-the-fact investigations of security incidents.","fix_text":"Ensure the VMM provides a report generation capability that supports after-the-fact investigations of security incidents.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM provides a report generation capability that supports after-the-fact investigations of security incidents.\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If the report generation capability does not support after-the-fact investigations, it is difficult to establish, correlate, and investigate the events leading up to an outage or attack or identify those responses for one. This capability is also required to comply with applicable Federal laws and DoD policies.\n\nThe report generation capability must support after-the-fact investigations of security incidents either natively or through the use of third-party tools.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-71381","V-57121"],"ccis":["CCI-001880"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"0fb31da8-ad5d-4bc9-982c-e37426edb6d2","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-207461","group_tree":[{"id":"V-207461","title":"SRG-OS-000353","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-207461","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM that provides an audit reduction capability must not alter original content or time ordering of audit records.","rule_id_src":"SV-207461r958776_rule","rule_id":"SV-207461r958776","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000353-VMM-001310","rule_title":"The VMM that provides an audit reduction capability must not alter original content or time ordering of audit records.","fix_text":"Configure the VMM that provides an audit reduction capability so that it does not alter original content or time ordering of audit records.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM that provides an audit reduction capability does not alter original content or time ordering of audit records.\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":" If the audit reduction capability alters the content or time ordering of audit records, the integrity of the audit records is compromised, and the records are no longer usable for forensic analysis.\n\nAudit reduction is a process that manipulates collected audit information and organizes such information in a summary format that is more meaningful to analysts. Time ordering refers to the chronological organization of records based on time stamps. The degree of time stamp precision can affect this.\n\nThis requirement is specific to VMMs providing audit reduction capabilities. The audit reduction capability can be met either natively or through the use of third-party tools.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-71383","V-57123"],"ccis":["CCI-001881"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"e49402b1-1d85-4b0a-97ba-f79bd78eac70","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-207462","group_tree":[{"id":"V-207462","title":"SRG-OS-000354","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-207462","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM that provides a report generation capability must not alter original content or time ordering of audit records.","rule_id_src":"SV-207462r987795_rule","rule_id":"SV-207462r987795","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000354-VMM-001320","rule_title":"The VMM that provides a report generation capability must not alter original content or time ordering of audit records.","fix_text":"Configure the VMM that provides a report generation capability so that it does not alter original content or time ordering of audit records.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM that provides a report generation capability does not alter original content or time ordering of audit records.\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If the report generation capability alters the content or time ordering of audit records, the integrity of the audit records is compromised, and the records are no longer usable for forensic analysis.\n\nTime ordering refers to the chronological organization of records based on time stamps. The degree of time stamp precision can affect this.\n\nThis requirement is specific to VMMs providing report generation capabilities. The report generation capability can be met either natively or through the use of third-party tools.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-71385","V-57125"],"ccis":["CCI-001882"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"cdba0c21-ddfe-422c-943e-c04ef5df81f4","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-207463","group_tree":[{"id":"V-207463","title":"SRG-OS-000355","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-207463","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM must, for networked systems, compare internal information system clocks at least every 24 hours with an authoritative time source.","rule_id_src":"SV-207463r1038976_rule","rule_id":"SV-207463r1038976","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000355-VMM-001330","rule_title":"The VMM must, for networked systems, compare internal information system clocks at least every 24 hours with an authoritative time source.","fix_text":"Configure the VMM, for networked systems, to compare internal information system clocks at least every 24 hours with an authoritative time source.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM, for networked systems, compares internal information system clocks at least every 24 hours with an authoritative time source.\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inaccurate time stamps make it more difficult to correlate events and can lead to an inaccurate analysis. Determining the correct time a particular event occurred on a system is critical when conducting forensic analysis and investigating system events. Sources outside of the configured acceptable allowance (drift) may be inaccurate.\n\nSynchronizing internal VMM clocks provides uniformity of time stamps for VMMs with multiple system clocks and systems connected over a network.\n\nOrganizations should consider endpoints that may not have regular access to the authoritative time server (e.g., mobile, teleworking, and tactical endpoints).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-71387","V-57127"],"ccis":["CCI-004923"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"ca82ef0b-4f1a-40f6-a2d4-44cd81fd9195","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-207464","group_tree":[{"id":"V-207464","title":"SRG-OS-000356","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-207464","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM must synchronize internal information system clocks to the authoritative time source when the time difference is greater than one second.","rule_id_src":"SV-207464r984238_rule","rule_id":"SV-207464r984238","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000356-VMM-001340","rule_title":"The VMM must synchronize internal information system clocks to the authoritative time source when the time difference is greater than one second.","fix_text":"Configure the VMM to synchronize internal information system clocks to the authoritative time source when the time difference is greater than one second.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM synchronizes internal information system clocks to the authoritative time source when the time difference is greater than one second.\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inaccurate time stamps make it more difficult to correlate events and can lead to an inaccurate analysis. Determining the correct time a particular event occurred on a system is critical when conducting forensic analysis and investigating system events. \n\nSynchronizing internal VMM clocks provides uniformity of time stamps for VMMs with multiple system clocks and systems connected over a network.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-71389","V-57129"],"ccis":["CCI-004926"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"a78eac30-f33d-46d5-9016-3679043b3262","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-207465","group_tree":[{"id":"V-207465","title":"SRG-OS-000358","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-207465","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM must record time stamps for audit records that meet a granularity of one second for a minimum degree of precision.","rule_id_src":"SV-207465r958786_rule","rule_id":"SV-207465r958786","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000358-VMM-001350","rule_title":"The VMM must record time stamps for audit records that meet a granularity of one second for a minimum degree of precision.","fix_text":"Configure the VMM to record time stamps for audit records that meet a granularity of one second for a minimum degree of precision.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM records time stamps for audit records that meet a granularity of one second for a minimum degree of precision.\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Without sufficient granularity of time stamps, it is not possible to adequately determine the chronological order of records. \n\nTime stamps generated by the VMM include date and time. Granularity of time measurements refers to the degree of synchronization between VMM clocks and reference clocks.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-71391","V-57131"],"ccis":["CCI-001889"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"57449094-2176-44ff-8c71-1827873af0ee","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-207466","group_tree":[{"id":"V-207466","title":"SRG-OS-000359","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-207466","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM must record time stamps for audit records that can be mapped to Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) or Greenwich Mean Time (GMT).","rule_id_src":"SV-207466r958788_rule","rule_id":"SV-207466r958788","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000359-VMM-001360","rule_title":"The VMM must record time stamps for audit records that can be mapped to Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) or Greenwich Mean Time (GMT).","fix_text":"Configure the VMM to record time stamps for audit records that can be mapped to Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) or Greenwich Mean Time (GMT).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM records time stamps for audit records that can be mapped to Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) or Greenwich Mean Time (GMT).\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If time stamps are not consistently applied and there is no common time reference, it is difficult to perform forensic analysis.\n\nTime stamps generated by the VMM include date and time. Time is commonly expressed in Coordinated Universal Time (UTC), a modern continuation of Greenwich Mean Time (GMT), or local time with an offset from UTC.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-71393","V-57133"],"ccis":["CCI-001890"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"e0cbbb30-e095-4889-a751-9ec6f23b8992","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-207467","group_tree":[{"id":"V-207467","title":"SRG-OS-000360","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-207467","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM must enforce dual authorization for movement and/or deletion of all audit information, when such movement or deletion is not part of an authorized automatic process.","rule_id_src":"SV-207467r958790_rule","rule_id":"SV-207467r958790","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000360-VMM-001370","rule_title":"The VMM must enforce dual authorization for movement and/or deletion of all audit information, when such movement or deletion is not part of an authorized automatic process.","fix_text":"Configure the VMM to enforce dual authorization for movement and/or deletion of all audit information, when such movement or deletion is not part of an authorized automatic process.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM enforces dual authorization for movement and/or deletion of all audit information, when such movement or deletion is not part of an authorized automatic process.\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"An authorized user may intentionally or accidentally move or delete audit records without those specific actions being authorized.\n\nAll bulk manipulation of audit information must be via authorized automatic processes. Any manual manipulation of audit information must require dual authorization. Dual authorization mechanisms require the approval of two authorized individuals in order to execute.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-71395","V-57135"],"ccis":["CCI-000366","CCI-001896"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"05ec4e25-d23e-40d9-ad4c-344f7c19c15b","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-207468","group_tree":[{"id":"V-207468","title":"SRG-OS-000362","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-207468","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM must prohibit user installation of software without explicit privileged status.","rule_id_src":"SV-207468r984239_rule","rule_id":"SV-207468r984239","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000362-VMM-001390","rule_title":"The VMM must prohibit user installation of software without explicit privileged status.","fix_text":"Configure the VMM to prohibit user installation of software or guest VMs without explicit privileged status.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM prohibits user installation of software or guest VMs without explicit privileged status.\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing regular users to install software or guest VMs, without explicit privileges, creates the risk that untested or potentially malicious software will be installed on the VMM. Explicit privileges (escalated or administrative privileges) provide the regular user with explicit capabilities and control that exceeds the rights of a regular user.\n\nVMM functionality will vary, and while users are not permitted to install unapproved software or guest VMs, there may be instances when the organization allows the user to install approved software packages such as from an approved software repository. \n\nThe VMM or software configuration management utility must enforce control of software installation by users based upon what types of software installations are permitted (e.g., updates and security patches to existing software) and what types of installations are prohibited (e.g., software whose pedigree with regard to being potentially malicious is unknown or suspect) by the organization.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-71397","V-57137"],"ccis":["CCI-003980"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"26e44ea1-e7c1-4b51-aecb-63d2daf8c26a","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-207469","group_tree":[{"id":"V-207469","title":"SRG-OS-000363","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-207469","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM must notify designated personnel if baseline configurations are changed in an unauthorized manner.","rule_id_src":"SV-207469r958794_rule","rule_id":"SV-207469r958794","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000363-VMM-001400","rule_title":"The VMM must notify designated personnel if baseline configurations are changed in an unauthorized manner.","fix_text":"Configure the VMM to notify designated personnel if baseline configurations are changed in an unauthorized manner.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM notifies designated personnel if baseline configurations are changed in an unauthorized manner.\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Unauthorized changes to the baseline configuration could make the VMM vulnerable to various attacks or allow unauthorized access to the VMM. Changes to VMM configurations can have unintended side effects, some of which may be relevant to security. \n\nDetecting such changes and providing an automated response can help avoid unintended, negative consequences that could ultimately affect the security state of the VMM. The VMM's IMO/ISSO and SAs must be notified via email and/or monitoring system trap when there is an unauthorized modification of a configuration item.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-71399","V-57139"],"ccis":["CCI-001744"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"a0d7a29d-1e11-41ad-99d0-4447257e717f","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-207470","group_tree":[{"id":"V-207470","title":"SRG-OS-000364","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-207470","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM must enforce access restrictions associated with changes to the system.","rule_id_src":"SV-207470r958796_rule","rule_id":"SV-207470r958796","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000364-VMM-001410","rule_title":"The VMM must enforce access restrictions associated with changes to the system.","fix_text":"Configure the VMM to enforce access restrictions associated with changes to the system.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM enforces access restrictions associated with changes to the system.\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Failure to provide logical access restrictions associated with changes to system configuration may have significant effects on the overall security of the system. \n\nWhen dealing with access restrictions pertaining to change control, it should be noted that any changes to the hardware, software, and/or firmware components of the VMM can potentially have significant effects on the overall security of the system. \n\nAccordingly, only qualified and authorized individuals should be allowed to obtain access to VMM components for the purposes of initiating changes, including upgrades and modifications. \n\nLogical access restrictions include, for example, controls that restrict access to guest VMs, workflow automation, media libraries, abstract layers (e.g., changes implemented into third-party interfaces rather than directly into VMMs), and change windows (e.g., changes occur only during specified times, making unauthorized changes easy to discover).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-71401","V-57141"],"ccis":["CCI-001813"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"fa85c6f5-fa37-4d74-9db4-1a3252046f70","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-207471","group_tree":[{"id":"V-207471","title":"SRG-OS-000365","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-207471","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM must audit the enforcement actions used to restrict access associated with changes to the system.","rule_id_src":"SV-207471r984240_rule","rule_id":"SV-207471r984240","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000365-VMM-001420","rule_title":"The VMM must audit the enforcement actions used to restrict access associated with changes to the system.","fix_text":"Configure the VMM to audit the enforcement actions used to restrict access associated with changes to the system.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM audits the enforcement actions used to restrict access associated with changes to the system.\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Without auditing the enforcement of access restrictions against changes to the VMM configuration, it will be difficult to identify attempted attacks, and an audit trail will not be available for forensic investigation for after-the-fact actions. \n\nEnforcement actions are the methods or mechanisms used to prevent unauthorized changes to configuration settings. Enforcement action methods may be as simple as denying access to a file based on the application of file permissions (access restriction). Audit items may consist of lists of actions blocked by access restrictions or changes identified after the fact.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-71403","V-57143"],"ccis":["CCI-003938"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"e11f3800-9cbc-458c-9279-8166099493cb","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-207472","group_tree":[{"id":"V-207472","title":"SRG-OS-000366","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-207472","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM must prevent the installation of guest VMs, patches, service packs, device drivers, or VMM components without verification they have been digitally signed using a certificate that is recognized and approved by the organization.","rule_id_src":"SV-207472r984242_rule","rule_id":"SV-207472r984242","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000366-VMM-001430","rule_title":"The VMM must prevent the installation of guest VMs, patches, service packs, device drivers, or VMM components without verification they have been digitally signed using a certificate that is recognized and approved by the organization.","fix_text":"Configure the VMM to prevent the installation of guest VMs, patches, service packs, device drivers, or VMM components without verification they have been digitally signed using a certificate that is recognized and approved by the organization.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM prevents the installation of guest VMs, patches, service packs, device drivers, or VMM components without verification they have been digitally signed using a certificate that is recognized and approved by the organization.\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Changes to any software components can have significant effects on the overall security of the VMM. This requirement ensures the software has not been tampered with and that it has been provided by a trusted vendor. \n\nAccordingly, guest VMs, patches, service packs, device drivers, or VMM components must be signed with a certificate recognized and approved by the organization. \n\nVerifying the authenticity of the software prior to installation validates the integrity of the patch or upgrade received from a vendor. This ensures the software has not been tampered with and that it has been provided by a trusted vendor. Self-signed certificates are disallowed by this requirement. The VMM should not have to verify the software again. This requirement does not mandate DOD certificates for this purpose; however, the certificate used to verify the software must be from an approved certificate authority (CA).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-71405","V-57145"],"ccis":["CCI-003992"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"dbff1497-0d7f-45f2-a6ea-6a6de0b14b99","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-207473","group_tree":[{"id":"V-207473","title":"SRG-OS-000368","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-207473","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM must prevent use of service and helper VMs not required to support proper VMM function.","rule_id_src":"SV-207473r958804_rule","rule_id":"SV-207473r958804","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000368-VMM-001440","rule_title":"The VMM must prevent use of service and helper VMs not required to support proper VMM function.","fix_text":"Configure the VMM to prevent use of service and helper VMs not required to support proper VMM function.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM prevents use of service and helper VMs not required to support proper VMM function.\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Control of program execution is a mechanism used to prevent execution of unauthorized programs. Some VMMs may provide a capability that runs counter to the mission or provides users with functionality that exceeds mission requirements. This includes functions and services installed at the VMM level.\n\nSome of the service and helper VMs, installed by default, may be harmful or may not be necessary to support essential organizational operations (e.g., key missions, functions). Removal of such VMs is not always possible; therefore, establishing a method of preventing VM activation is critical to maintaining a secure system baseline.\n\nMethods for complying with this requirement include restricting execution of VMs in certain environments, while preventing execution in other environments; or limiting execution of certain VM functionality based on organizationally defined criteria (e.g., privileges, subnets, sandboxed environments, or roles).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-71407","V-57147"],"ccis":["CCI-001764"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"3e233fa9-920b-41b7-8d3d-9c2a5cb57469","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-207474","group_tree":[{"id":"V-207474","title":"SRG-OS-000368","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-207474","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM must prevent inappropriate use of redundant guest VMs.","rule_id_src":"SV-207474r958804_rule","rule_id":"SV-207474r958804","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000368-VMM-001450","rule_title":"The VMM must prevent inappropriate use of redundant guest VMs.","fix_text":"Configure the VMM to prevent inappropriate use of redundant guest VMs.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM prevents inappropriate use of redundant guest VMs.\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Control of program execution is a mechanism used to prevent execution of unauthorized programs. Some VMMs may provide a capability that runs counter to the mission or provides users with functionality that exceeds mission requirements. This includes functions and services installed at the VMM level. \n\nSome of the guest VMs, set up for redundancy, may be harmful or may not be necessary to support essential organizational operations (e.g., key missions, functions) at the present time. Removal of such VMs is not always possible; therefore, establishing a method of preventing VM activation is critical to maintaining a secure system baseline.\n\nMethods for complying with this requirement include restricting execution of VMs in certain environments, while preventing execution in other environments; or limiting execution of certain VM functionality based on organizationally defined criteria (e.g., privileges, subnets, sandboxed environments, or roles).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-71409","V-57149"],"ccis":["CCI-001764"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"93a91731-2a65-46f7-9467-f135f7955f6f","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-207475","group_tree":[{"id":"V-207475","title":"SRG-OS-000370","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-207475","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM must employ a deny-all, permit-by-exception policy to allow the execution of authorized software programs and guest VMs.","rule_id_src":"SV-207475r958808_rule","rule_id":"SV-207475r958808","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000370-VMM-001460","rule_title":"The VMM must employ a deny-all, permit-by-exception policy to allow the execution of authorized software programs and guest VMs.","fix_text":"Configure the VMM to employ a deny-all, permit-by-exception policy to allow the execution of authorized software programs and guest VMs.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM employs a deny-all, permit-by-exception policy to allow the execution of authorized software programs and guest VMs.\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Utilizing a whitelist provides a configuration management method for allowing the execution of only authorized software and guest VMs. Using only authorized software decreases risk by limiting the number of potential vulnerabilities and by preventing the execution of malware.\n\nThe organization must identify authorized software programs and permit execution of authorized software. The process used to identify software programs and guest VMs that are authorized to execute on organizational VMMs is commonly referred to as whitelisting.\n\nVerification of white-listed software and guest VMs can occur either prior to execution or at system startup.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-71411","V-57151"],"ccis":["CCI-001774"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"00782bbd-d39f-4ccf-a620-e15e048f63df","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-207480","group_tree":[{"id":"V-207480","title":"SRG-OS-000375","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-207480","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM must implement multifactor authentication for remote access to privileged accounts such that one of the factors is provided by a device separate from the system gaining access.","rule_id_src":"SV-207480r984255_rule","rule_id":"SV-207480r984255","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000375-VMM-001510","rule_title":"The VMM must implement multifactor authentication for remote access to privileged accounts such that one of the factors is provided by a device separate from the system gaining access.","fix_text":"Configure the VMM to implement multifactor authentication for remote access to privileged accounts such that one of the factors is provided by a device separate from the system gaining access.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM implements multifactor authentication for remote access to privileged accounts such that one of the factors is provided by a device separate from the system gaining access.\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Using an authentication device, such as a CAC or token that is separate from the VMM, ensures that even if the VMM is compromised, that compromise will not affect credentials stored on the authentication device. \n\nMultifactor solutions that require devices separate from VMMs gaining access include, for example, hardware tokens providing time-based or challenge-response authenticators and smart cards such as the U.S. Government Personal Identity Verification card and the DOD common access card.\n\nA privileged account is defined as a VMM account with authorizations of a privileged user.\n\nRemote access is access to DOD nonpublic VMMs by an authorized user (or a VMM) communicating through an external, non-organization-controlled network. Remote access methods include, for example, dial-up, broadband, and wireless.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-71421","V-57161"],"ccis":["CCI-004046"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"edfe3107-e495-4aff-8a19-81021e85b697","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-207481","group_tree":[{"id":"V-207481","title":"SRG-OS-000376","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-207481","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM must accept Personal Identity Verification (PIV) credentials.","rule_id_src":"SV-207481r958816_rule","rule_id":"SV-207481r958816","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000376-VMM-001520","rule_title":"The VMM must accept Personal Identity Verification (PIV) credentials.","fix_text":"Configure the VMM to accept Personal Identity Verification (PIV) credentials.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM accepts Personal Identity Verification (PIV) credentials.\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The use of PIV credentials facilitates standardization and reduces the risk of unauthorized access.\n\nDoD has mandated the use of the CAC to support identity management and personal authentication for systems covered under Homeland Security Presidential Directive (HSPD) 12 and as a primary component of layered protection for national security systems.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-71423","V-57163"],"ccis":["CCI-001953"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"aa33b279-db5b-4d38-b8a6-390bda6a03ba","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-207482","group_tree":[{"id":"V-207482","title":"SRG-OS-000377","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-207482","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM must electronically verify Personal Identity Verification (PIV) credentials.","rule_id_src":"SV-207482r958818_rule","rule_id":"SV-207482r958818","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000377-VMM-001530","rule_title":"The VMM must electronically verify Personal Identity Verification (PIV) credentials.","fix_text":"Configure the VMM to electronically verify Personal Identity Verification (PIV) credentials.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM electronically verifies Personal Identity Verification (PIV) credentials.\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The use of PIV credentials facilitates standardization and reduces the risk of unauthorized access.\n\nDoD has mandated the use of the CAC to support identity management and personal authentication for systems covered under Homeland Security Presidential Directive (HSPD) 12 and as a primary component of layered protection for national security systems.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-71425","V-57165"],"ccis":["CCI-001954"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"b00c8c9c-f953-4b91-b4e2-eb6527242393","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-207483","group_tree":[{"id":"V-207483","title":"SRG-OS-000378","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-207483","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM must authenticate peripherals before establishing a connection.","rule_id_src":"SV-207483r958820_rule","rule_id":"SV-207483r958820","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000378-VMM-001540","rule_title":"The VMM must authenticate peripherals before establishing a connection.","fix_text":"Configure the VMM to authenticate peripherals before establishing a connection.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM authenticates peripherals before establishing a connection.\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Without authenticating devices, unidentified or unknown devices may be introduced, thereby facilitating malicious activity.\n\nPeripherals include, but are not limited to, such devices as flash drives, external storage, and printers.\n\nThis requirement is applicable to devices capable of authentication.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-71427","V-57167"],"ccis":["CCI-001958"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"05770749-d6c6-43ed-87b6-da5ed44c46ed","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-207484","group_tree":[{"id":"V-207484","title":"SRG-OS-000379","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-207484","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM must authenticate all endpoint devices before establishing a local, remote, and/or network connection using bidirectional authentication that is cryptographically based.","rule_id_src":"SV-207484r971545_rule","rule_id":"SV-207484r971545","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000379-VMM-001550","rule_title":"The VMM must authenticate all endpoint devices before establishing a local, remote, and/or network connection using bidirectional authentication that is cryptographically based.","fix_text":"Configure the VMM to authenticate all endpoint devices before establishing a local, remote, and/or network connection using bidirectional authentication that is cryptographically based.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM authenticates all endpoint devices before establishing a local, remote, and/or network connection using bidirectional authentication that is cryptographically based.\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Without authenticating devices, unidentified or unknown devices may be introduced, thereby facilitating malicious activity. Bidirectional authentication provides stronger safeguards to validate the identity of other devices for connections that are of greater risk.\n\nBidirectional authentication solutions include, but are not limited, to IEEE 802.1x and Extensible Authentication Protocol [EAP], Radius server with EAP-Transport Layer Security [TLS] authentication, Kerberos, and SSL mutual authentication.\n\nA local connection is any connection with a device communicating without the use of a network. A network connection is any connection with a device that communicates through a network (e.g., local area network, wide area network, or the Internet). A remote connection is any connection with a device communicating through an external network (e.g., the Internet).\n\nBecause of the challenges of applying this requirement on a large scale, organizations are encouraged to only apply this requirement to those limited number (and type) of devices that truly need to support this capability.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-71529","V-57269"],"ccis":["CCI-001967"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"80cf30dc-b398-42aa-bbd7-2aaae06f08c9","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-207486","group_tree":[{"id":"V-207486","title":"SRG-OS-000383","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-207486","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM must prohibit the use of cached authenticators after one day.","rule_id_src":"SV-207486r958828_rule","rule_id":"SV-207486r958828","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000383-VMM-001570","rule_title":"The VMM must prohibit the use of cached authenticators after one day.","fix_text":"Configure the VMM to prohibit the use of cached authenticators after one day.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM prohibits the use of cached authenticators after one day.\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If cached authentication information is out of date, the validity of the authentication information may be questionable.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-71533","V-57273"],"ccis":["CCI-002007"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"cc3f1f9c-722a-4526-84f4-9edc07960419","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-207487","group_tree":[{"id":"V-207487","title":"SRG-OS-000384","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-207487","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM, for PKI-based authentication, must implement a local cache of revocation data to support path discovery and validation in case of the inability to access revocation information via the network.","rule_id_src":"SV-207487r984257_rule","rule_id":"SV-207487r984257","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000384-VMM-001580","rule_title":"The VMM, for PKI-based authentication, must implement a local cache of revocation data to support path discovery and validation in case of the inability to access revocation information via the network.","fix_text":"Configure the VMM, for PKI-based authentication, to implement a local cache of revocation data to support path discovery and validation in case of the inability to access revocation information via the network.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM, for PKI-based authentication, implements a local cache of revocation data to support path discovery and validation in case of the inability to access revocation information via the network.\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Without configuring a local cache of revocation data, there is the potential to allow access to users who are no longer authorized (users with revoked certificates).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-71535","V-57275"],"ccis":["CCI-004068"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"4bba68d8-796c-4979-97d9-7288f34b369b","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-207488","group_tree":[{"id":"V-207488","title":"SRG-OS-000396","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-207488","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM must implement NSA-approved cryptography to protect classified information in accordance with applicable federal laws, Executive Orders, directives, policies, regulations, and standards.","rule_id_src":"SV-207488r987791_rule","rule_id":"SV-207488r987791","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000396-VMM-001590","rule_title":"The VMM must implement NSA-approved cryptography to protect classified information in accordance with applicable federal laws, Executive Orders, directives, policies, regulations, and standards.","fix_text":"Configure the VMM to implement NSA-approved cryptography to protect classified information in accordance with applicable federal laws, Executive Orders, directives, policies, regulations, and standards.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM implements NSA-approved cryptography to protect classified information in accordance with applicable federal laws, Executive Orders, directives, policies, regulations, and standards.\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Use of weak or untested encryption algorithms undermines the purposes of utilizing encryption to protect data. The VMM must implement cryptographic modules adhering to the higher standards approved by the federal government since this provides assurance they have been tested and validated.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-71537","V-57277"],"ccis":["CCI-002450"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"83e902b2-d4bd-4d37-b2fd-5de2f4f6d443","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-207489","group_tree":[{"id":"V-207489","title":"SRG-OS-000399","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-207489","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM must request data origin authentication verification on the name/address resolution responses the system receives from authoritative sources.","rule_id_src":"SV-207489r958860_rule","rule_id":"SV-207489r958860","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000399-VMM-001600","rule_title":"The VMM must request data origin authentication verification on the name/address resolution responses the system receives from authoritative sources.","fix_text":"Configure the VMM to request data origin authentication verification on the name/address resolution responses the system receives from authoritative sources.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM requests data origin authentication verification on the name/address resolution responses the system receives from authoritative sources.\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If data origin authentication and data integrity verification is not performed, the resultant response could be forged, it may have come from a poisoned cache, the packets could have been intercepted without the resolver's knowledge, or resource records could have been removed which would result in query failure or DoS. Data origin authentication must be performed to thwart these types of attacks.\n\nEach client of name resolution services either performs this validation on its own, or has authenticated channels to trusted validation providers. VMMs that provide name and address resolution services for local clients include, for example, recursive resolving or caching Domain Name System (DNS) servers. DNS client resolvers either perform validation of DNSSEC signatures, or clients use authenticated channels to recursive resolvers that perform such validations. VMMs that use technologies other than the DNS to map between host/service names and network addresses provide other means to enable clients to verify the authenticity of response data.\n\nThis is not applicable if DNSSEC is not implemented on the local network.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-71539","V-57279"],"ccis":["CCI-002465"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"72835663-5563-4f6e-a7bb-90a1308aed92","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-207490","group