he local network.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-71541","V-57281"],"ccis":["CCI-002466"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"37cda114-6e70-4a5b-83fe-04b46a151e0c","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-207491","group_tree":[{"id":"V-207491","title":"SRG-OS-000401","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-207491","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM must perform data integrity verification on the name/address resolution responses the system receives from authoritative sources.","rule_id_src":"SV-207491r958864_rule","rule_id":"SV-207491r958864","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000401-VMM-001620","rule_title":"The VMM must perform data integrity verification on the name/address resolution responses the system receives from authoritative sources.","fix_text":"Configure the VMM to perform data integrity verification on the name/address resolution responses the system receives from authoritative sources.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM performs data integrity verification on the name/address resolution responses the system receives from authoritative sources.\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If data origin authentication and data integrity verification are not performed, the resultant response could be forged, it may have come from a poisoned cache, the packets could have been intercepted without the resolver's knowledge, or resource records could have been removed which would result in query failure or denial of service. Data integrity verification must be performed to thwart these types of attacks.\n\nEach client of name resolution services either performs this validation on its own, or has authenticated channels to trusted validation providers. VMMs that provide name and address resolution services for local clients include, for example, recursive resolving or caching Domain Name System (DNS) servers. DNS client resolvers either perform validation of DNSSEC signatures, or clients use authenticated channels to recursive resolvers that perform such validations.\n\nThis is not applicable if DNSSEC is not implemented on the local network.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-71543","V-57283"],"ccis":["CCI-002467"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"a0085f01-d21b-4edc-b2cf-375a58aec5c7","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-207492","group_tree":[{"id":"V-207492","title":"SRG-OS-000402","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-207492","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM must perform data origin verification authentication on the name/address resolution responses the system receives from authoritative sources.","rule_id_src":"SV-207492r958866_rule","rule_id":"SV-207492r958866","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000402-VMM-001630","rule_title":"The VMM must perform data origin verification authentication on the name/address resolution responses the system receives from authoritative sources.","fix_text":"Configure the VMM to perform data origin verification authentication on the name/address resolution responses the system receives from authoritative sources.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM performs data origin verification authentication on the name/address resolution responses the system receives from authoritative sources.\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If data origin authentication and data integrity verification are not performed, the resultant response could be forged, it may have come from a poisoned cache, the packets could have been intercepted without the resolver's knowledge, or resource records could have been removed which would result in query failure or denial of service. Data origin authentication verification must be performed to thwart these types of attacks.\n\nEach client of name resolution services either performs this validation on its own or has authenticated channels to trusted validation providers. VMMs that provide name and address resolution services for local clients include, for example, recursive resolving or caching Domain Name System (DNS) servers. DNS client resolvers either perform validation of DNSSEC signatures, or clients use authenticated channels to recursive resolvers that perform such validations.\n\nThis is not applicable if DNSSEC is not implemented on the local network.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-71545","V-57285"],"ccis":["CCI-002468"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"65cc296c-2614-47c6-9f2b-07a417b4fe10","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-207493","group_tree":[{"id":"V-207493","title":"SRG-OS-000403","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-207493","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM must only allow the use of DoD PKI-established certificate authorities for verification of the establishment of protected sessions.","rule_id_src":"SV-207493r958868_rule","rule_id":"SV-207493r958868","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000403-VMM-001640","rule_title":"The VMM must only allow the use of DoD PKI-established certificate authorities for verification of the establishment of protected sessions.","fix_text":"Configure the VMM to only allow the use of DoD PKI-established certificate authorities for verification of the establishment of protected sessions.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM only allows the use of DoD PKI-established certificate authorities for verification of the establishment of protected sessions.\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Untrusted Certificate Authorities (CA) can issue certificates, but they may be issued by organizations or individuals that seek to compromise DoD systems or by organizations with insufficient security controls. If the CA used for verifying the certificate is not a DoD-approved CA, trust of this CA has not been established.\n\nThe DoD will only accept PKI certificates obtained from a DoD-approved internal or external certificate authority. Reliance on CAs for the establishment of secure sessions includes, for example, the use of SSL/TLS certificates.\n\nThis requirement is not applicable to VMM-internal sessions between components not identified as \"Key Terrain\" for \"Non-Person Entities\" per DoD policy.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-71547","V-57287"],"ccis":["CCI-002470"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"82e78fec-c830-403e-b14a-3e24d9edd470","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-207494","group_tree":[{"id":"V-207494","title":"SRG-OS-000404","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-207494","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM must implement cryptographic mechanisms to prevent unauthorized modification of all information at rest on all VMM components.","rule_id_src":"SV-207494r958870_rule","rule_id":"SV-207494r958870","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000404-VMM-001650","rule_title":"The VMM must implement cryptographic mechanisms to prevent unauthorized modification of all information at rest on all VMM components.","fix_text":"Configure the VMM to implement cryptographic mechanisms to prevent unauthorized modification of all information at rest on all VMM components.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM implements cryptographic mechanisms to prevent unauthorized modification of all information at rest on all VMM components.\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"VMMs handling data requiring \"data at rest\" protections must employ cryptographic mechanisms to prevent unauthorized modification of the information at rest.\n\nSelection of a cryptographic mechanism is based on the need to protect the integrity of organizational information. The strength of the mechanism is commensurate with the security category and/or classification of the information.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-71549","V-57289"],"ccis":["CCI-002475"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"e9f2826a-f526-415f-ab78-d31bfa8ee63f","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-207495","group_tree":[{"id":"V-207495","title":"SRG-OS-000405","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-207495","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM must implement cryptographic mechanisms to prevent unauthorized disclosure of all information at rest on all VMM components.","rule_id_src":"SV-207495r958872_rule","rule_id":"SV-207495r958872","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000405-VMM-001660","rule_title":"The VMM must implement cryptographic mechanisms to prevent unauthorized disclosure of all information at rest on all VMM components.","fix_text":"Configure the VMM to implement cryptographic mechanisms to prevent unauthorized disclosure of all information at rest on all VMM components.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM implements cryptographic mechanisms to prevent unauthorized disclosure of all information at rest on all VMM components.\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"VMMs handling data requiring \"data at rest\" protections must employ cryptographic mechanisms to prevent unauthorized disclosure of the information at rest.\n\nSelection of a cryptographic mechanism is based on the need to protect the integrity of organizational information. The strength of the mechanism is commensurate with the security category and/or classification of the information.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-71551","V-57291"],"ccis":["CCI-002476"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"f68f97e4-73e3-4614-9fad-b13e2539c1cc","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-207496","group_tree":[{"id":"V-207496","title":"SRG-OS-000408","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-207496","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM must maintain a separate execution domain for each executing process.","rule_id_src":"SV-207496r958878_rule","rule_id":"SV-207496r958878","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000408-VMM-001670","rule_title":"The VMM must maintain a separate execution domain for each executing process.","fix_text":"Configure the VMM to maintain a separate execution domain for each executing process.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM maintains a separate execution domain for each executing process.\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"VMMs can maintain separate execution domains for each executing process by assigning each process a separate address space. Each VMM process has a distinct address space so that communication between processes is performed in a manner controlled through the security functions, and one process cannot modify the executing code of another process. Maintaining separate execution domains for executing processes can be achieved, for example, by implementing separate address spaces. This capability is available in most commercial VMMs that employ multistate processor technologies.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-71553","V-57293"],"ccis":["CCI-002530"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"6edf55fd-377b-4ee0-9c20-49b092c45988","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-207497","group_tree":[{"id":"V-207497","title":"SRG-OS-000408","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-207497","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM must maintain a separate execution domain for each guest VM.","rule_id_src":"SV-207497r958878_rule","rule_id":"SV-207497r958878","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000408-VMM-001680","rule_title":"The VMM must maintain a separate execution domain for each guest VM.","fix_text":"Configure the VMM to maintain a separate execution domain for each guest VM.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM maintains a separate execution domain for each guest VM.\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"VMMs can maintain separate execution domains for each executing guest VM by assigning each guest VM a separate address space. Each VMM guest VM has a distinct address space so that communication between guest VMs is performed in a manner controlled through the security functions of the VMM, and one guest VM cannot modify the executing code of another guest VM. This capability is available in most commercial VMMs that employ virtualization processor technologies.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-71555","V-57295"],"ccis":["CCI-002530"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"a625b371-4e0f-4fa3-bce6-b6c3017fd10f","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-207498","group_tree":[{"id":"V-207498","title":"SRG-OS-000420","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-207498","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM must protect against or limit the effects of Denial of Service (DoS) attacks by ensuring the VMM is implementing rate-limiting measures on impacted network interfaces.","rule_id_src":"SV-207498r958902_rule","rule_id":"SV-207498r958902","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000420-VMM-001690","rule_title":"The VMM must protect against or limit the effects of Denial of Service (DoS) attacks by ensuring the VMM is implementing rate-limiting measures on impacted network interfaces.","fix_text":"Configure the VMM to protect against or limit the effects of Denial of Service (DoS) attacks by ensuring the VMM is implementing rate-limiting measures on impacted network interfaces.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM protects against or limit the effects of Denial of Service (DoS) attacks by ensuring the VMM is implementing rate-limiting measures on impacted network interfaces.\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"DoS is a condition when a resource is not available for legitimate users. When this occurs, the organization either cannot accomplish its mission or must operate at degraded capacity.\n\nThis requirement addresses the configuration of the VMM to mitigate the impact of DoS attacks that have occurred or are ongoing on system availability. For each system, known and potential DoS attacks must be identified and solutions for each type implemented. A variety of technologies exist to limit or, in some cases, eliminate the effects of DoS attacks (e.g., limiting processes or establishing memory partitions). Employing increased capacity and bandwidth, combined with service redundancy, may reduce the susceptibility to some DoS attacks, though they may also exacerbate the problem.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-71557","V-57297"],"ccis":["CCI-002385"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"70b5868b-1239-44c1-94e9-8f47b0feabd2","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-207499","group_tree":[{"id":"V-207499","title":"SRG-OS-000423","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-207499","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM must protect the confidentiality and integrity of transmitted information.","rule_id_src":"SV-207499r958908_rule","rule_id":"SV-207499r958908","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000423-VMM-001700","rule_title":"The VMM must protect the confidentiality and integrity of transmitted information.","fix_text":"Configure the VMM to protect the confidentiality and integrity of transmitted information.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM protects the confidentiality and integrity of transmitted information.\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Without protection of the transmitted information, confidentiality and integrity may be compromised as unprotected communications can be intercepted and either read or altered. \n\nThis requirement applies to both internal and external networks and all types of VMM components from which information can be transmitted (e.g., guest VMs, servers, mobile devices, notebook computers, printers, copiers, scanners, and facsimile machines). Communication paths outside the physical protection of a controlled boundary are exposed to the possibility of interception and modification. \n\nProtecting the confidentiality and integrity of organizational information can be accomplished by physical means (e.g., employing physical distribution systems) or by logical means (e.g., employing cryptographic techniques). If physical means of protection are employed, then logical means (cryptography) do not have to be employed, and vice versa.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-71559","V-57299"],"ccis":["CCI-002418"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"b7b7d6e6-4267-4d5e-a00c-73026270b35f","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-207500","group_tree":[{"id":"V-207500","title":"SRG-OS-000425","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-207500","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM must maintain the confidentiality and integrity of information during preparation for transmission.","rule_id_src":"SV-207500r958912_rule","rule_id":"SV-207500r958912","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000425-VMM-001710","rule_title":"The VMM must maintain the confidentiality and integrity of information during preparation for transmission.","fix_text":"Configure the VMM to maintain the confidentiality and integrity of information during preparation for transmission.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM maintains the confidentiality and integrity of information during preparation for transmission.\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Information can be either unintentionally or maliciously disclosed or modified during preparation for transmission, for example, during aggregation, at protocol transformation points, and during packing/unpacking. These unauthorized disclosures or modifications compromise the confidentiality or integrity of the information.\n\nEnsuring the confidentiality of transmitted information requires the VMM to take measures in preparing information for transmission. This can be accomplished via access control and encryption.\n\nUse of this requirement will be limited to situations where the data owner has a strict requirement for ensuring data integrity and confidentiality is maintained at every step of the data transfer and handling process. When transmitting data, VMMs need to support transmission protection mechanisms such as TLS, SSL VPNs, or IPSEC.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-71561","V-57301"],"ccis":["CCI-002420"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"1e951d63-6b86-429e-9c4c-17e02073ad34","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-207501","group_tree":[{"id":"V-207501","title":"SRG-OS-000426","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-207501","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM must maintain the confidentiality and integrity of information during reception.","rule_id_src":"SV-207501r958914_rule","rule_id":"SV-207501r958914","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000426-VMM-001720","rule_title":"The VMM must maintain the confidentiality and integrity of information during reception.","fix_text":"Configure the VMM to maintain the confidentiality and integrity of information during reception.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM maintains the confidentiality and integrity of information during reception.\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Information can be either unintentionally or maliciously disclosed or modified during reception, including, for example, during de-aggregation, at protocol transformation points, and during packing/unpacking. These unauthorized disclosures or modifications compromise the confidentiality or integrity of the information.\n\nEnsuring the confidentiality of transmitted information requires the VMM to take measures in preparing information during reception. This can be accomplished via access control and encryption.\n\nUse of this requirement will be limited to situations where the data owner has a strict requirement for ensuring data integrity and confidentiality is maintained at every step of the data transfer and handling process. When receiving data, VMMs need to leverage protection mechanisms such as TLS, SSL VPNs, or IPSEC.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-71563","V-57303"],"ccis":["CCI-002422"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"8e1eabc2-2a0d-455e-8c03-3dbbdd6f9fd2","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-207502","group_tree":[{"id":"V-207502","title":"SRG-OS-000432","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-207502","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM must behave in a predictable and documented manner that reflects organizational and system objectives when invalid inputs are received.","rule_id_src":"SV-207502r958926_rule","rule_id":"SV-207502r958926","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000432-VMM-001730","rule_title":"The VMM must behave in a predictable and documented manner that reflects organizational and system objectives when invalid inputs are received.","fix_text":"Ensure the VMM behaves in a predictable and documented manner that reflects organizational and system objectives when invalid inputs are received.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM behaves in a predictable and documented manner that reflects organizational and system objectives when invalid inputs are received.\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A common vulnerability of VMM is unpredictable behavior when invalid inputs are received. This requirement guards against adverse or unintended system behavior caused by invalid inputs, where VMM responses to the invalid input may be disruptive or cause the system to fail into an unsafe state.\n\nThe behavior will be derived from the organizational and system requirements and includes, but is not limited to, notification of the appropriate personnel, creating an audit record, and rejecting invalid input.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-71565","V-57305"],"ccis":["CCI-002754"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"7ed56bef-9f34-4532-871c-53d501004bfc","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-207503","group_tree":[{"id":"V-207503","title":"SRG-OS-000433","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-207503","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM must implement non-executable data to protect its memory from unauthorized code execution.","rule_id_src":"SV-207503r958928_rule","rule_id":"SV-207503r958928","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000433-VMM-001740","rule_title":"The VMM must implement non-executable data to protect its memory from unauthorized code execution.","fix_text":"Configure the VMM to implement non-executable data to protect its memory from unauthorized code execution.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM implements non-executable data to protect its memory from unauthorized code execution.\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some adversaries launch attacks with the intent of executing code in non-executable regions of memory or in memory locations that are prohibited. Data execution prevention safeguards can either be hardware-enforced or software-enforced with hardware providing the greater strength of mechanism.\n\nExamples of attacks are buffer overflow attacks.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-71567","V-57307"],"ccis":["CCI-002824"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"5b9b495c-8045-44c7-864d-bdbd63199dfd","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-207504","group_tree":[{"id":"V-207504","title":"SRG-OS-000433","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-207504","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM must implement address space layout randomization to protect its memory from unauthorized code execution.","rule_id_src":"SV-207504r958928_rule","rule_id":"SV-207504r958928","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000433-VMM-001750","rule_title":"The VMM must implement address space layout randomization to protect its memory from unauthorized code execution.","fix_text":"Configure the VMM to implement address space layout randomization to protect its memory from unauthorized code execution.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM implements address space layout randomization to protect its memory from unauthorized code execution.\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some adversaries launch attacks with the intent of executing code in non-executable regions of memory or in memory locations that are prohibited. Data execution prevention safeguards can either be hardware-enforced or software-enforced with hardware providing the greater strength of mechanism.\n\nExamples of attacks are buffer overflow attacks.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-71569","V-57309"],"ccis":["CCI-002824"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"586cb33f-5b6d-4314-bc0c-a83a15fbe328","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-207505","group_tree":[{"id":"V-207505","title":"SRG-OS-000437","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-207505","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM must remove all software components after updated versions have been installed.","rule_id_src":"SV-207505r958936_rule","rule_id":"SV-207505r958936","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000437-VMM-001760","rule_title":"The VMM must remove all software components after updated versions have been installed.","fix_text":"Configure the VMM to remove all software components after updated versions have been installed.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM removes all software components after updated versions have been installed.\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Previous versions of software components that are not removed from the VMM after updates have been installed may be exploited by adversaries. Some information technology products may remove older versions of software automatically from the VMM.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-71571","V-57311"],"ccis":["CCI-002617"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"9a04661e-0b99-46b4-9409-102cb3a8108b","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-207506","group_tree":[{"id":"V-207506","title":"SRG-OS-000445","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-207506","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM must verify correct operation of all security functions.","rule_id_src":"SV-207506r958944_rule","rule_id":"SV-207506r958944","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000445-VMM-001780","rule_title":"The VMM must verify correct operation of all security functions.","fix_text":"Configure the VMM to verify correct operation of all security functions.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM verifies correct operation of all security functions.\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Without verification of the security functions, security functions may not operate correctly and the failure may go unnoticed. Security function is defined as the hardware, software, and/or firmware of the VMM responsible for enforcing the system security policy and supporting the isolation of code and data on which the protection is based. Security functionality includes, but is not limited to, establishing system accounts, configuring access authorizations (i.e., permissions, privileges), setting events to be audited, and setting intrusion detection parameters.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-71573","V-57313"],"ccis":["CCI-002696"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"505c1094-1f35-4491-ac4f-4bbd93b52641","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-207507","group_tree":[{"id":"V-207507","title":"SRG-OS-000446","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-207507","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM must perform verification of the correct operation of security functions: upon system startup and/or restart; upon command by a user with privileged access; and/or every 30 days.","rule_id_src":"SV-207507r958946_rule","rule_id":"SV-207507r958946","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000446-VMM-001790","rule_title":"The VMM must perform verification of the correct operation of security functions: upon system startup and/or restart; upon command by a user with privileged access; and/or every 30 days.","fix_text":"Configure the VMM to perform verification of the correct operation of security functions: upon system startup and/or restart; upon command by a user with privileged access; and/or every 30 days.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM performs verification of the correct operation of security functions: upon system startup and/or restart; upon command by a user with privileged access; and/or every 30 days.\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Without verification of the security functions, security functions may not operate correctly and the failure may go unnoticed. Security function is defined as the hardware, software, and/or firmware of the VMM responsible for enforcing the system security policy and supporting the isolation of code and data on which the protection is based. Security functionality includes, but is not limited to, establishing system accounts, configuring access authorizations (i.e., permissions, privileges), setting events to be audited, and setting intrusion detection parameters.\n\nNotifications provided by VMMs include, for example, electronic alerts to system administrators, messages to local computer consoles, and/or hardware indications, such as lights.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-71575","V-57315"],"ccis":["CCI-002699"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"eec69d80-0326-4012-ba3b-6f4f7c68af6c","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-207508","group_tree":[{"id":"V-207508","title":"SRG-OS-000447","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-207508","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM must shut down, restart, and/or notify the system administrator when anomalies in the operation of any security functions are discovered.","rule_id_src":"SV-207508r958948_rule","rule_id":"SV-207508r958948","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000447-VMM-001800","rule_title":"The VMM must shut down, restart, and/or notify the system administrator when anomalies in the operation of any security functions are discovered.","fix_text":"Configure the VMM to shut down, restart, and/or notify the system administrator when anomalies in the operation of any security functions are discovered.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM shuts down, restarts, and/or notifies the system administrator when anomalies in the operation of any security functions are discovered.\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"If anomalies are not acted upon, security functions may fail to secure the system. \n\nSecurity function is defined as the hardware, software, and/or firmware of the VMM responsible for enforcing the system security policy and supporting the isolation of code and data on which the protection is based. Security functionality includes, but is not limited to, establishing system accounts, configuring access authorizations (i.e., permissions, privileges), setting events to be audited, and setting intrusion detection parameters.\n\nNotifications provided by VMMs include messages to local computer consoles, hardware indications, such as lights, and/or notifying SAs via email or monitoring system traps.\n\nThis capability must take into account operational requirements for availability when selecting an appropriate response. The organization may choose to shut down or restart the VMM or send notifications to SAs upon security function anomaly detection.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-71577","V-57317"],"ccis":["CCI-002702"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"decf1394-980c-4630-a95b-25fdcf626c65","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-207509","group_tree":[{"id":"V-207509","title":"SRG-OS-000458","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-207509","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM must generate audit records when successful/unsuccessful attempts to access security objects occur.","rule_id_src":"SV-207509r958968_rule","rule_id":"SV-207509r958968","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000458-VMM-001810","rule_title":"The VMM must generate audit records when successful/unsuccessful attempts to access security objects occur.","fix_text":"Configure the VMM to generate audit records when successful/unsuccessful attempts to access security objects occur.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM generates audit records when successful/unsuccessful attempts to access security objects occur.\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Without generating audit records that are specific to the security and mission needs of the organization, it would be difficult to establish, correlate, and investigate the events relating to an incident or identify those responsible for one. \n\nAudit records can be generated from various components within the VMM (e.g., module or policy filter).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-71579","V-57319"],"ccis":["CCI-000172"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"b3cdfa84-6a4a-43af-87c1-9653fd8f03c7","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/