_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Use of weak or untested encryption algorithms undermines the purposes of utilizing encryption to protect data. The VMM must implement cryptographic modules adhering to the higher standards approved by the federal government since this provides assurance they have been tested and validated.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-71613","V-57353"],"ccis":["CCI-002450"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"11a188a5-2c13-4748-8003-6acb7025e6a6","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-207527","group_tree":[{"id":"V-207527","title":"SRG-OS-000479","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-207527","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM must, at a minimum, off-load interconnected systems in real time and off-load standalone systems weekly.","rule_id_src":"SV-207527r959008_rule","rule_id":"SV-207527r959008","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000479-VMM-001990","rule_title":"The VMM must, at a minimum, off-load interconnected systems in real time and off-load standalone systems weekly.","fix_text":"Configure the VMM to, at a minimum, off-load interconnected systems in real time and off-load standalone systems weekly.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM, at a minimum, off-loads interconnected systems in real time and off-loads standalone systems weekly.\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Information stored in one location is vulnerable to accidental or incidental deletion or alteration.\n\nOff-loading is a common process in VMMs with limited audit storage capacity.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-71615","V-57355"],"ccis":["CCI-001851"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"9101483b-bd96-42ee-ad91-00df6ec08ffa","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-207528","group_tree":[{"id":"V-207528","title":"SRG-OS-000480","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-207528","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM must be configured in accordance with the security configuration settings based on DoD security configuration or implementation guidance, including STIGs, NSA configuration guides, CTOs, and DTMs.","rule_id_src":"SV-207528r959010_rule","rule_id":"SV-207528r959010","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000480-VMM-002000","rule_title":"The VMM must be configured in accordance with the security configuration settings based on DoD security configuration or implementation guidance, including STIGs, NSA configuration guides, CTOs, and DTMs.","fix_text":"Configure the VMM to be configured in accordance with the security configuration settings based on DoD security configuration or implementation guidance, including STIGs, NSA configuration guides, CTOs, and DTMs.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM is configured in accordance with the security configuration settings based on DoD security configuration or implementation guidance, including STIGs, NSA configuration guides, CTOs, and DTMs.\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Configuring the VMM to implement organization-wide security implementation guides and security checklists ensures compliance with federal standards and establishes a common security baseline across DoD that reflects the most restrictive security posture consistent with operational requirements.\n\nConfiguration settings are the set of parameters that can be changed in hardware, software, or firmware components of the system that affect the security posture and/or functionality of the system. Security-related parameters are those parameters impacting the security state of the system, including the parameters required to satisfy other security control requirements. Security-related parameters include, for example: registry settings; account, file, directory permission settings; and settings for functions, ports, protocols, services, and remote connections.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-71617","V-57357"],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"172015d9-59e5-4517-8ee6-7fd3370ca8cf","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-207529","group_tree":[{"id":"V-207529","title":"SRG-OS-000481","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-207529","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM must protect the confidentiality and integrity of communications with wireless peripherals.","rule_id_src":"SV-207529r958358_rule","rule_id":"SV-207529r958358","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000481-VMM-002010","rule_title":"The VMM must protect the confidentiality and integrity of communications with wireless peripherals.","fix_text":"Configure the VMM to protect the confidentiality and integrity of communications with wireless peripherals.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM protects the confidentiality and integrity of communications with wireless peripherals.\n\nIf it does not, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Without protection of communications with wireless peripherals, confidentiality and integrity may be compromised because unprotected communications can be intercepted and either read, altered, or used to compromise the VMM.\nThis requirement applies to wireless peripheral technologies (e.g., wireless mice, keyboards, displays, etc.) used with a VMM. Wireless peripherals (e.g., Wi-Fi/Bluetooth/IR keyboards, mice, pointing devices, and Near Field Communications [NFC]) present a unique challenge by creating an open, unsecured port on a computer. Wireless peripherals must meet DoD requirements for wireless data transmission and be approved for use by the AO. Even though some wireless peripherals, such as mice and pointing devices, do not ordinarily carry information that needs to be protected, modification of communications with these wireless peripherals may be used to compromise the VMM. Communication paths outside the physical protection of a controlled boundary are exposed to the possibility of interception and modification.\nProtecting the confidentiality and integrity of communications with wireless peripherals can be accomplished by physical means (e.g., employing physical barriers to wireless radio frequencies) or by logical means (e.g., employing cryptographic techniques). If physical means of protection are employed, then logical means (cryptography) do not have to be employed, and vice versa. If the wireless peripheral is only passing telemetry data, encryption of the data may not be required.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-79197","V-64707"],"ccis":["CCI-002418"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"f4f35684-21f3-419a-a678-809709e46690","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-264315","group_tree":[{"id":"V-264315","title":"SRG-OS-000590","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-264315","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM must disable accounts when the accounts are no longer associated to a user.","rule_id_src":"SV-264315r984260_rule","rule_id":"SV-264315r984260","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000590-VMM-000110","rule_title":"The VMM must disable accounts when the accounts are no longer associated to a user.","fix_text":"Configure the VMM to disable accounts when the accounts are no longer associated to a user.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM is configured to disable accounts when the accounts are no longer associated to a user.\n\nIf the VMM is not configured to disable accounts when the accounts are no longer associated to a user, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Disabling expired, inactive, or otherwise anomalous accounts supports the concepts of least privilege and least functionality which reduce the attack surface of the system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-003628"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"c02ca3c1-bb80-4dd1-a4be-31e3da168a75","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-264316","group_tree":[{"id":"V-264316","title":"SRG-OS-000690","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-264316","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM must prohibit the use or connection of unauthorized hardware components.","rule_id_src":"SV-264316r984263_rule","rule_id":"SV-264316r984263","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000690-VMM-000140","rule_title":"The VMM must prohibit the use or connection of unauthorized hardware components.","fix_text":"Configure the VMM to prohibit the use or connection of unauthorized hardware components.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM is configured to prohibit the use or connection of unauthorized hardware components.\n\nIf the VMM is not configured to prohibit the use or connection of unauthorized hardware components, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Hardware components provide the foundation for organizational systems and the platform for the execution of authorized software programs. Managing the inventory of hardware components and controlling which hardware components are permitted to be installed or connected to organizational systems is essential to provide adequate security.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-003959"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"38431179-dbf8-453e-aa46-489a167be614","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-264317","group_tree":[{"id":"V-264317","title":"SRG-OS-000705","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-264317","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM must implement multifactor authentication for local, network, and/or remote access to privileged accounts and/or nonprivileged accounts such that the device meets organization-defined strength of mechanism requirements.","rule_id_src":"SV-264317r984266_rule","rule_id":"SV-264317r984266","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000705-VMM-000150","rule_title":"The VMM must implement multifactor authentication for local, network, and/or remote access to privileged accounts and/or nonprivileged accounts such that the device meets organization-defined strength of mechanism requirements.","fix_text":"Configure the VMM to implement multifactor authentication for local, network, and/or remote access to privileged accounts and/or nonprivileged accounts such that the device meets organization-defined strength of mechanism requirements.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM is configured to implement multifactor authentication for local, network, and/or remote access to privileged accounts and/or nonprivileged accounts such that the device meets organization-defined strength of mechanism requirements.\n\nIf the VMM is not configured to implement multifactor authentication for local, network, and/or remote access to privileged accounts and/or nonprivileged accounts such that the device meets organization-defined strength of mechanism requirements, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The purpose of requiring a device separate from the system to which the user is attempting to gain access for one of the factors during multifactor authentication is to reduce the likelihood of compromising authenticators or credentials stored on the system. Adversaries may be able to compromise such authenticators or credentials and subsequently impersonate authorized users. Implementing one of the factors on a separate device (e.g., a hardware token), provides a greater strength of mechanism and an increased level of assurance in the authentication process.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-004047"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"5dcdd01d-b6c7-4478-b983-91bf6c1f5e15","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-264318","group_tree":[{"id":"V-264318","title":"SRG-OS-000710","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-264318","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM must for password-based authentication, verify when users create or update passwords the passwords are not found on the list of commonly-used, expected, or compromised passwords in ia-5 (1) (a).","rule_id_src":"SV-264318r984269_rule","rule_id":"SV-264318r984269","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000710-VMM-000160","rule_title":"The VMM must for password-based authentication, verify when users create or update passwords the passwords are not found on the list of commonly-used, expected, or compromised passwords in ia-5 (1) (a).","fix_text":"Configure the VMM to verify when users create or update passwords the passwords are not found on the list of commonly-used, expected, or compromised passwords in ia-5 (1) (a).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM is configured to verify when users create or update passwords the passwords are not found on the list of commonly-used, expected, or compromised passwords in ia-5 (1) (a).\n\nIf the VMM is not configured to verify when users create or update passwords the passwords are not found on the list of commonly-used, expected, or compromised passwords in ia-5 (1) (a), this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Password-based authentication applies to passwords regardless of whether they are used in single-factor or multifactor authentication. Long passwords or passphrases are preferable over shorter passwords. Enforced composition rules provide marginal security benefits while decreasing usability. However, organizations may choose to establish certain rules for password generation (e.g., minimum character length for long passwords) under certain circumstances and can enforce this requirement in IA-5(1)(h). Account recovery can occur, for example, in situations when a password is forgotten. Cryptographically protected passwords include salted one-way cryptographic hashes of passwords. The list of commonly used, compromised, or expected passwords includes passwords obtained from previous breach corpuses, dictionary words, and repetitive or sequential characters. The list includes context-specific words, such as the name of the service, username, and derivatives thereof.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-004061"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"8d80af28-027d-4b4a-b1d2-816b6cdb4b0e","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-264319","group_tree":[{"id":"V-264319","title":"SRG-OS-000720","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-264319","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM must for password-based authentication, require immediate selection of a new password upon account recovery.","rule_id_src":"SV-264319r984272_rule","rule_id":"SV-264319r984272","rule_version":"SRG-OS-000720-VMM-000170","rule_title":"The VMM must for password-based authentication, require immediate selection of a new password upon account recovery.","fix_text":"Configure the VMM to require immediate selection of a new password upon account recovery.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the VMM is configured to require immediate selection of a new password upon account recovery.\n\nIf the VMM is not configured to require immediate selection of a new password upon account recovery, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Virtual_Machine_Manager_SRG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Password-based authentication applies to passwords regardless of whether they are used in single-factor or multifactor authentication. Long passwords or passphrases are preferable over shorter passwords. Enforced composition rules provide marginal security benefits while decreasing usability. However, organizations may choose to establish certain rules for password generation (e.g., minimum character length for long passwords) under certain circumstances and can enforce this requirement in IA-5(1)(h). Account recovery can occur, for example, in situations when a password is forgotten. Cryptographically protected passwords include salted one-way cryptographic hashes of passwords. The list of commonly used, compromised, or expected passwords includes passwords obtained from previous breach corpuses, dictionary words, and repetitive or sequential characters. The list includes context-specific words, such as the name of the service, username, and derivatives thereof.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-004063"],"reference_identifier":"2924","uuid":"2384c696-6c5a-4a7c-93f3-51f5f49325fd","stig_uuid":"a72c3068-7635-4929-ba84-370ae1b4c32c","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG answer file is providing the below comment on 03/08/2026:\r\n\nAnswer File: '/tmp/Evaluate-STIG_RemoteComputer/AnswerFiles/XCP-ng_v8.3_VMM_AnswerFile.xml'\r\nKey Name: XCP-ng\r\nIndex: 1\r\n\r\n[ValidTrueComment]:\r\n\n"},{"group_id_src":"V-264320","group_tree":[{"id":"V-264320","title":"SRG-OS-000725","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-264320","severity":"medium","group_title":"The VMM must for password-based authent